# Observability & Debuggability Audit

## Overview
Evaluates whether system behavior can be understood and debugged in production.

## Focus Areas

### Logging Quality
- Structured logging (not free-form noise)
- Appropriate log levels
- No sensitive data leakage

### Traceability
- Request tracing across services
- Correlation IDs present

### Error Context
- Actionable error messages
- Stack trace hygiene
- Debug metadata availability

### Metrics & Monitoring
- Key business metrics present
- System health metrics tracked
- Alerting hooks available

### Production Debuggability
- Ability to reconstruct failures
- Replay or trace workflows

## Output Decision
- GOOD
- INSUFFICIENT_OBSERVABILITY
- CRITICAL_GAP
